What is S3?
Amazon S3 is an object storage service used to store and retrieve any amount of data from anywhere.

Key Features:
Unlimited Storage
High Durability (11 9's)
High Availability
Versioning
Lifecycle Management
Encryption

S3 Components:
Bucket
Container for storing objects.

Example:
company-production-images
company-backups
devops-logs

Object
Actual file stored inside bucket.

Example:
image.jpg
backup.zip
logs.txt

Storage Classes:

Standard
Frequently accessed data.

Standard-IA
Infrequent access.

Glacier Instant Retrieval
Archived data.

Glacier Deep Archive
Long-term backup.

Real-Time Scenario:
E-Commerce Website

Customer Uploads Product Image
            ↓
           S3
            ↓
Website Displays Image

Millions of images can be stored efficiently.

